<span id="xxv.iii.iii.xvii"></span>

<span id="xxv.iii.iii.xvii-p1"></span> <span class="c10"><span
id="xxv.iii.iii.xvii-p1.1"></span>From Letter XXII <span
id="fr_4522"></span>[4523](#fn_4522) </span>.—*(For 350..md)*

<span id="xxv.iii.iii.xvii-p3"></span><span class="c10"><span
id="xxv.iii.iii.xvii-p3.1"></span>Where</span> our Lord Jesus Christ,
who took upon Him to die for all, stretched forth His hands, not
somewhere on the earth beneath, but in the air itself, in order that the
Salvation effected by the Cross might be shewn to be for all men
everywhere: destroying the devil who was working in the air: and that He
might consecrate our road up to Heaven, and make it free.

